text: Chamcook Mountain is located from St. Andrews, Charlotte County, New Brunswick, Canada. Ice has completely ground over it and the summit, above sea level, is scored and polished. ==Etymology== Chamcook is derived from the Passamaquoddy word of K'tchumcook which, according to William Francis Ganong, has many meanings but none are certain. ==References== Category:Landforms of Charlotte County, New Brunswick Category:Mountains of New Brunswick
title: Chamcook Mountain
